<div id=3D"scoringabowlinggameoverview" class=3D"section_text">
<ul>
<li>Score a spare by adding 10 points to the number of pins you knock over =
on your next roll, says bowling expert Chad McLean.</li>
<li>Score a strike by adding 10 points to the number of pins you knock over=
 on your next 2 rolls.</li>
<li>If you don=E2=80=99t knock down all the pins, your score is the total n=
umber of pins you did knock over.</li>
</ul>
