<div class=3D"step_num" aria-hidden=3D"true">2</div><div class=3D"step">
<b class=3D"whb" aria-hidden=3D"true">Write the number of pins you knocked =
down each roll in the small boxes.</b> Each player gets to bowl twice in ea=
ch turn except in the last (tenth) frame, unless they knock over all the pi=
ns with their first roll (in which case they only bowl once that turn). Wri=
te the number of pins you knock over on your first roll in the small, left-=
hand box at the top of that turn=E2=80=99s frame. Then, record the number o=
f pins you knock over on your second roll in the right-hand box.<sup id=3D"=
_ref-2" class=3D"reference" aria-label=3D"Link to Reference 2"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://www.wikihow.com/Score-Bowling#_note-2">[2]</a>
</sup>
<ul>
<li>For example, if you knock over 2 pins on your first bowl, write the num=
eral =E2=80=9C2=E2=80=9D in the upper left box. On your second bowl, if you=
 knock over 4 more, write =E2=80=9C4=E2=80=9D in the right-hand box.</li>
<li>Be sure to only write down how many pins you knocked over on your secon=
d roll in the right-hand box, <b>not</b> the total number of pins you knock=
ed down that turn.</li>
<li>Each player will bowl a maximum of 21 times per game.</li>
</ul>
