<div class=3D"step_num" aria-hidden=3D"true">1</div><div class=3D"step">
<b class=3D"whb" aria-hidden=3D"true">Write your total score in the current=
 frame after your turn.</b> If there are still any pins standing after the =
second roll of your turn, this is known as an =E2=80=9Copen frame.=E2=80=9D=
 Add the number of pins you knocked over on your first and second rolls (th=
e numbers you wrote in the 2 small boxes of the frame), then add that sum t=
o your total score to find your current score. Write your current score in =
the large box for that frame.<sup id=3D"_ref-6" class=3D"reference" aria-la=
bel=3D"Link to Reference 6"><a href=3D"https://www.wikihow.com/Score-Bowlin=
g#_note-6">[6]</a>
</sup>
<ul><li>For example, if you knocked over 5 pins on your first roll and 4 pi=
ns on your second, you earned 9 points that frame. Then, if you had 30 poin=
ts before, add your 9 points to 30 for a total score of 39.</li></ul>
