<div class=3D"step_num" aria-hidden=3D"true">3</div><div class=3D"step">
<b class=3D"whb" aria-hidden=3D"true">Score a strike by adding 10 to your n=
ext 2 rolls.</b> Just as with a spare, hold off on scoring a strike (when y=
ou knock down all of the pins on your first roll) until after you complete =
your next turn. Then, add 10 points to the sum of your next 2 rolls.<sup id=
=3D"_ref-9" class=3D"reference trusted" aria-label=3D"Link to Reference 9">=
<a href=3D"https://www.wikihow.com/Score-Bowling#_note-9">[9]</a>
</sup><sup id=3D"_ref-10" class=3D"reference" aria-label=3D"Link to Referen=
ce 10"><a href=3D"https://www.wikihow.com/Score-Bowling#_note-10">[10]</a>
</sup>
<ul>
<li>For example, let's say you get a strike in turn 1. In turn 2, you roll =
a 2 and a 6, for a total of 8 points. Once you finish turn 2, your score fo=
r turn 1 is 18; 10 (for the strike) +8 (in turn 2). Then, add 18+8 for a to=
tal current score of 26</li>
<li>If you <a href=3D"https://www.wikihow.com/Bowl-a-Strike" title=3D"Bowl =
a Strike"> roll a strike</a> on each of your first 3 turns, the first strik=
e is worth 30 (10 for the strike, + 10 for each of the next 2 strikes). The=
 second strike is worth 20 (10 for the strike, + 10 for the strike in turn =
3) + the score of the first roll of your fourth turn.</li>
</ul>
</div>
